            <p>Demonstrates a race condition when rapidly clicking the button.</p>
            <p id="buggy-count">Count: 0</p>
            <button id="buggy-button">Increment</button>
            <p><strong>Why does this happen?</strong> When you rapidly click the button, multiple <code>setTimeout</code> calls are made. These asynchronous updates read the current count, increment it, and then write it back. If one update hasn't written its value yet and another update reads the count, it will read an outdated value, causing the displayed count to fall behind or show wrong values.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="version">
            <h2>Corrected Version</h2>
            <p>Resolves the race condition by directly updating the count without reading it first.</p>
            <p id="corrected-count">Count: 0</p>
            <button id="corrected-button">Increment</button>
